{"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"patternMatch"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"stringLength","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"string","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"stringReversed"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar"},{"text":">? = nil) -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Passing the correct"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"length of the string given is mandatory. The reversed string can be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"omitted by passing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NULL"},{"text":", this is more efficient if the reversed","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"version of the string to be matched is not at hand, as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_pattern_match()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will only construct it if the compiled pattern","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"requires reverse matches."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that, if the user code will (possibly) match a string against a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"multitude of patterns containing wildcards, chances are high that","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"some patterns will require a reversed string. In this case, it’s","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"more efficient to provide the reversed string to avoid multiple"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"constructions thereof in the various calls to "},{"code":"g_pattern_match()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note also that the reverse of a UTF-8 encoded string can in general"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"not be obtained by [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.strreverse","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"]. This works only if the string","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"does not contain any multibyte characters. GLib offers the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.utf8_strreverse","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] function to reverse UTF-8 encoded strings."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"pattern_match is deprecated:","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use [method@GLib.PatternSpec.match] instead"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","platforms":[],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"patternMatch","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"stringLength"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"string","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeId